[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":557},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2022\u002F03\u002F06\u002Fmongoose-middleware-19\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2022\u002F03\u002F06\u002Fmongoose-middleware-19\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2022\u002F03\u002F06\u002Fmongoose-middleware-19\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2022\u002F03\u002F06\u002Fmongoose-middleware-19\u002F":533,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2022\u002F03\u002F06\u002Fmongoose-middleware-19\u002F":542},"\u002Fnodejs\u002F20220306\u002F287448729\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":514,"date":515,"description":516,"extension":517,"lang":518,"meta":519,"navigation":91,"path":520,"readingMinutes":521,"seo":522,"standalone":523,"stem":524,"tags":525,"tldr":530,"updated":515,"url":531,"__hash__":532},"content\u002Fen\u002FNodejs\u002Fmongoose-middleware-19.md","Mongoose Has Middleware Too? Hooking Into save with pre and post","1003199279",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":510},"minimark",[11,16,20,24,27,35,189,195,319,328,335,344,488,494,500,506],[12,13,15],"h2",{"id":14},"intro","Intro",[17,18,19],"p",{},"Hold on — Mongoose has Middleware too! Middleware is basically a middle layer: before you enter or do something, you have to pass through it first. And it turns out Mongoose's Middleware is really handy.",[12,21,23],{"id":22},"middleware","Middleware",[17,25,26],{},"Like I just said, the idea of Middleware is that before you enter or do something, you always pass through this middle layer first. On the backend, the most common example is checking whether a user is logged in, or whether their Token is still valid, before letting them into a router.",[17,28,29,30,34],{},"Mongoose itself supports Middleware too. For example, say I want to output some text right before I save data. You'd write it like this — and remember, this goes in ",[31,32,33],"code",{},"model\u002FUser.js",":",[36,37,42],"pre",{"className":38,"code":39,"langu